      <main class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds" role="main" id="main">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Connect a device to GovWifi</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">
          Create a GovWifi account and connect to a GovWifi network. Your device will connect to the wifi automatically in thousands of buildings that offer GovWifi.
        </p>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">1. Create a GovWifi account</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">You can either:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>text 'Go' to 07537 417 417</li>
          <li>send a blank email from your public sector email address to <%= link_to "signup@wifi.service.gov.uk", "mailto:signup@wifi.service.gov.uk", class: "govuk-link" %></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="govuk-body">We'll reply with your username and password. Do not share your details with anyone else.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">If you have any problems signing up, you can <a href="connect-to-govwifi/get-help-connecting/" class="govuk-link">get help connecting</a>.</p>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">2. Connect your device</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">By connecting to GovWifi, you accept our <a class="govuk-link" href="privacy-notice">privacy notice</a> and <a href="terms-and-conditions" class="govuk-link">terms and conditions</a>.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body"> To connect your device, follow the guide for
          <a class="govuk-link" href="/device-android">Android</a>,
          <a class="govuk-link" href="/device-iphone-or-ipad">iPhone or iPad</a>,
          <a class="govuk-link" href="/device-mac">Mac</a>,
          <a class="govuk-link" href="/device-windows">Windows</a> or
          <a class="govuk-link" href="/device-chromebook">Chromebook</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">You can use the same username and password to connect all your devices to GovWifi.</p>
        <div class="govuk-inset-text">
          If you manage IT services in a public sector organisation and want to provide GovWifi in your buildings, see how to <%= link_to "offer GovWifi", "https://docs.wifi.service.gov.uk/", class: "govuk-link" %>.
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </div>
